joke_list:
Astronaut 1: Hey mate, I can't find any milk for my coffee 
 Astronaut 2: In space, no one can. Here, use cream
A ghost floats into a bar and asks for a double gin & tonic. Bartender says "Sorry we don't serve spirits"

How do you turn a duck into a soul singer?
Put it inthe oven and wait 'till it's Bill Withers
Man walks into a bar, puts down a slab of concrete and says, "Can I have a beer, and one for the road too"

What do you call birds that are stuck together?
 "Vel-Crows"

Descartes walks into a bar and orders a drink.
 When he finishes, the bartender asks if he wants another.
 Descartes replies, "No, I think not!" and - *poof!* he disappears.

What do you call and Italian with a rubber toe?
 Roberto!

Q: How did the Caret escape prison?
 A: It's an escape character.
If a witch needs to modify one her existing spells, does she use a hex editor?

I went to the zoo and saw a baguette in a cage.
 The zookeeper said it was bread in captivity.

Q: Why do chicken coops have two doors?
 A: Because if they had four it would be a chicken sedan.

Q: What do you call a priest that graduated law school?
 A: Father in law.

Q: Why haven't aliens visited Earth?
 A: They've read the reviews. We have only one star.
Scientists got bored watching the earth turn, so after 24 hours they called it a day.
A programmer was arressted for writing unreadable code. He refused to comment.

Q: What does the 'S' in IoT stand for?
 A: Security.

What is the difference between illegal and unlawful?
 A: One of them is against the law and the other is a sick bird.

Q: How do you make a water bed more bouncy?
 A: Add spring water.
A termite walks into a bar and asks "Is your bar tender here?"

Q: What's the best part about living in Switzerland?
 A: I don't know, but the flag is a big plus.
My dad cried when he opened his 60th birthday card and said "One would have been enough"

Q: What's the difference between in-laws and outlaws?
 A: Outlaws are wanted.

Q: Did you hear about the scarecrow that won an award?
 A: He was just outstanding in his field.
To the man who stole my install disk for Microsoft Office - I will find you, you have my Word!
A man walks into a zoo. The only animal there is a dog. It's a Shih Tzu.
Got pulled over by the cops the other day. They asked me if I had a police record. I said no but I got plenty of sting records.
My dad always used to say "When one door closes, another one opens." Great man, terrible cabinet maker

Q: What do you call a deer without an eye?
 A: No-eye-deer.
A three legged dog walks into a saloon, and says "I'm lookin' for the man who show my paw."
I don't trust stairs. They are always up to something.

Q: What do you say to a nosy pepper?
 A: Japaeno business!

Q: What's the difference between roast beef and pea soup?
 A: Anyone can roast beef.
